chargeHist.descr: 1st Degree Child Sex Assault - Sexual Contact with Person under Age of 13

result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan L. Flick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st Degree Child Sex Assault - Sexual Contact with Person under Age of 13, a class B felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(1)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: If Probation or Extended Supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

miscConds.notes: PAYABLE DIRECTLY TO AND COLLECTED BY EAU CLAIRE COUNTY CLERK OF COURT.  NOT A CONDITION OF PROBATION.

No contact with K.N. or his family.
No unsupervised contact with anyone under the age of 18 years old.
Not to consume or possess any alcohol or enter any bars, taverns, or liquor stores.
Not to use or possess any illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia or non-prescribed medications.

Comply with any conditions/programming per agent.
Complete sex offender and mental health assessments and follow-through with recommendations.
Take medications as prescribed and only as prescribed.
Provide DNA sample and pay fee.
Register and comply with Sex Offender Registry for his lifetime.
Obtain high school diploma or it's equivalent.

timeConds.notes:
10 months stayed for agent to use at his/her discretion if defendant is not compliant while on probation.

30 days may be served by 240 hours of community service.  (Defendant chooses community service).  
DOC to find a place for defendant to do community service- if unable to place defendant due to the type of charge, defendant must serve it as jail time.  
DOC to notify Court of community service status.

30 days to be served initally and to begin no later than noon on May 18, 2015.

Huber granted for any reason the jail determines he is eligible.
